column15:
The tweet that uses a Distort tactic is:

@EmmanuelMacron If the Russians are a "brotherly nation of Ukrainians" and there is no crime of genocide, then Macron must also say that the Islamic terrorists who carried out the terrorist attacks in France were his brothers, and there were no terrorist attacks as such. S.Sternenko

This tweet attempts to alter the main message of the topic, which is providing support and defense to Ukraine, by introducing a comparison to terrorist attacks in France and questioning Macron's stance.

column17:
The posts that use the Distract tactic are:

@EmmanuelMacron Merci 🇫🇷
@EmmanuelMacron Good luck!✌️
@EmmanuelMacron Thank you!

These posts are distractions because they are not related to the topic of defense or the urgency of the situation in Mariupol. Instead, they are generic expressions of gratitude and good wishes, which divert attention away from the main issue at hand. Furthermore, they do not contribute to the conversation about providing necessary support and aid to the children in Mariupol who are in immediate danger.
